 in  isa investigationsedit in  when psagot was still owned by bank leumi the israel securities authority launched an investigation into the firms dealings for suspected violations of the regulation of investment advice and investment portfolio management law  the investigation went on for a year and culminated in a raid of psagots offices and the taking in of the firms executives for questioning in late  the impetus for the investigation was a psagot fund having raised nis billion in a single day psagot founder and general manager gabriella ravid resigned along with her deputy in late  in  bank leumi agreed to pay a fine of nis million as part of a plea bargain agreement in  police arrested three senior psagot employees on charges that they were involved in manipulating the prices of government and corporate bonds in order to redound greater profits to the firm and inflate their bonuses in the years – an investigation conducted by the isa concluded with psagot agreeing to pay a fine of nis0 million as part of a plea bargain0 psagot ceo at the time roy vermus was subsequently compelled to resign from the firm after the supreme court rejected an appeal he filed against his forced ouster from the company see alsoedit economy of israel venture capital in israel referencesedit  gewirtz jason  february 0 israels business elite weigh irans nuclear threat cnbc retrieved  february 0   contact us psagot investment house retrieved  february 0   psagot group – israel’s largest investment house duns  retrieved  february 0   a b bergman roee  december  ravid silbiger quit psagot ofek globes retrieved  march 0   dagan ram  november  york capital buys leumis psagot ofek haaretz retrieved  february 0   rochvarger michael  october  apax takeover of psagot falls apart haaretz retrieved  february 0   psagot buyout boosts private equity total to twoyear high globes  february 0 retrieved  march 0   a b peer eran  december  roy vermus leaves psagot globes retrieved  march 0   hazani gola